        <abstract>
            <p>Congratulates HES on producing an authoritative document [BAAS committee report on zoological nomenclature].</p> 
<p>Has been to N. Wales looking at glacier traces described by W. Buckland, which are most interesting and clear. Has written an article on what he saw ["Ancient glaciers of Caernarvonshire" (1842), <hi rend="italic">Collected papers</hi> 1: 163–71].</p> 
        </abstract>
